    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Abildgaardia megastachys are anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities, which are primarily attributed to its bioactive compounds. The antiseptic and antifungal properties of this plant are due to the presence of sesquiterpenes and flavonoids, which are effective against various pathogens and microorganisms. Moreover, Abildgaardia megastachys has been found to exhibit antioxidant activity, thanks to the presence of phenolic compounds and saponins, which help protect cells from oxidative damage. The plant also possesses anti-diabetic properties, which are mediated by the bioactive compound withanolides, that help regulate blood sugar levels. Additionally, the antiviral properties of Abildgaardia megastachys are attributed to the presence of volatile oils, which are effective against various viral infections.",
