    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Abildgaardia megastachys are infusion, tincture, tea, decoction, and salve. Infusion is a liquid preparation of the plant's flowers, leaves, or stems, typically made by steeping them in hot water. Tincture, on the other hand, is a concentrated liquid preparation made by soaking the plant material in a solvent, such as ethanol or glycerin. Decoction is a liquid preparation made by boiling the plant's roots, stems, or bark in water, often used for roots and bark that are difficult to infuse. Salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant material in a carrier oil, such as coconut or olive oil, often used for skin conditions.",
